als covering the preparation, characterization, and sterilization steps as well as transport phenomena. The different strategies pursued for the development of membrane bioartifi cial organs, including crucial issues related to blood/cell-membrane interactions are described with the aim of opening new and exciting frontiers in the coming decades. The book is a valuable tool for tissue engineers, clinicians, biomaterials scientists, membranologists as well as biologists and biotechnologists. It is also a source of reference for students, academic and industrial researchers in the topic of biotechnology, biomedical engineering, materials science and medicine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMembranes (Biology). 4aBiomaterialien. 4aChemische Technik. 4aMaterialwissenschaften. 4aRegenerative Medizin. 7aMEDICAL / Allied Health Services / Medical Technology.2bisacsh  aBioartificial Organs.  aBiomedical Technology.  aMaterials Science.  aMolecular Biology.  aRegenerative Medicine.1 aCurcio, Efrem, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDrioli, Enrico, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry,  Materials Sc, Geosc 2017z9783110548235oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831103908890 cprintz978311026798340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311026801040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110268010423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110268010.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE E